-----<br>
What do you mean exactly by kickarse ?<br>
Powerful ? No<br>
Useful to the realm ? Yes<br>
The skald main role is to provide speed, which is useful to the realm war in general, but isn't really useful to &quot;kick arse&quot;.<br>
However, as the rest of your questions seems to revolve about how skald compares in fighting situations, I have to warn you that you probably wont find them &quot;kickarse&quot;. Take that as whining if you want, you have been warned <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :rolleyes --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/eyes.gif ALT=":rolleyes"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  . Don't come to the skald class because you assume we are tank with speed, you'll be sorely disappointed (unless your goal is only to play skald on the battlegrounds, they do well in that level range).<br>
If you enjoy the &quot;bigger picture&quot;, and accept to sacrifice personal fulfillment to give a benefit to your realm, skald may be a good class for you.<br>
<br>
Are they useful in different scenarios such as keep taking/defense<br>
------<br>
No. If you want to be able to do anything in a siege, invest in lifter and learn siegecrafting.<br>
You have no song useful at range (700 on your shout is not enough to be useful on keep walls). You are like any no-range tank here, minus you don't have shield to block archers, etc ...<br>
Honestly, it is my no1 gripe with the skald class.<br>
<br>
1on1 combat<br>
-----<br>
Depends against what and who, RR, equipment, but globally skalds are a mediocre dueling class.<br>
<br>
group vs group<br>
-----<br>
Skald main selling point here. A skald has its role in an effective gank group : speed, and useful shouts to complement the backbone of a gank group (pac healer, damage dealers ...)<br>
<br>
How well can we fare against different classes such as tanks, hybrids, etc.<br>
-----<br>
Poorly. Not horrible, we can deal damage, but certainly not our forte (essentialy due to abysmal defense).<br>
<br>
We are roughly on the same hp and weaponskill table than any ohter hybrid/clerical class/stealther. <br>
<br>
We have the benefit over wardens or minstrels to be able to spec in 2h weapons. Our damage add and DD shouts adds up with our base damage nicely (though the effectiveness of DD shouts has been drastically reduced over the time, as 50% body resists in buffed groups are very common).<br>
<br>
Our defense however is quite bad. Chain, evade I, but parry that is necessarily specced very low (we don't have the points, unlike, say, LW champions or 2H thanes), no speccable shields, and no &quot;defensive&quot; chants/powers (unlike paladin, wardnes ...).<br>
Basically, when you consider either light tanks/assassins/friars with high evades (and generally parries, except assassins), or heavy tanks/most hybrids (with speccable shields and higher parries), our defense is at tha bottom of the scale. Even wardens and minstrels have PBT/ablative to make up from low defensive skills.<br>
<br>
Also we don't have self and castable buffs like many hybrids out there (from friars to wardens to champions to thanes), who can bump those classes hp and weaponskill closer to a tank's.<br>
<br>
The general feeling is that our OK offensive capabilities, which are acceptable compared to many hybrids out there (though dedicated damage dealers like friars, or offensively specced champions, or thanes have better offense), are not quite a compensation for our low survivability (we drop extremely fast if we are subject to enemy aggro. Healer or shamans &quot;outsurvive&quot; us on the battlefield easily).<br>
<br>
How well can we melee without having our songs suck<br>
-----<br>
46-47 weapon if you don't want to sacrifice songs. If you want to give up on your songs, you can spec weapon to 50, but you won't have access to best shout and best damage add.<br>
<br>
I hear we are good for groups but how about solo?<br>
-----<br>
If you want to solo, play an assassin. Honestly. The time were skalds were soloing at the gorge is what ... 1 year ago ? Unless you already are at the top realm ranks, but if you are rolling a skald, I doubt it.<br>
If you have a dedicated group, you can go skald.<br>
<br>
<br>
Since we can use two handers its worth using?, want to use two handed sword. <br>
-----<br>
Yes. 2H damage bonus &gt; unspecced small shield.<br>
Be aware that sword skill is flawed however. If you have a competitive or number crunching state of mind, I'd suggest considering either hammer or axe.<br>
<br>
Oh and btw please dont post if your one of those people that bitch n complain n moan about your class. I've read through this board and theres just too much of it. And you know what, just about EVERY single class board has people whining about their class<br>
-----<br>
Aye, we love you too, welcome to those boards (/sigh). We have good reasons to complain, and, as you are asking a lot of general and vague questions which show that you don't know what skalds can do, and how they do compare (not a flame, it is ok and it is the purpose of those boards, we'll be happy to answer you), you don't really have any elements to judge our attitude. The issues, bugs, and proposed fixes are essentially well known, and it will not be hard to deal with them easily (as the community and our TL have already made a lot of work to track out the bugs, propose revamps to the battlesong spec, etc ...). But all of this is met by a deafening silence.<br>
