<br>
Skalds are pure offense. The main defense in RvR-Melee is a shield. Skalds can't specc those. Even if parry is fixed it won't save you from beeing hit a lot of times. You can't parry 2-3 people like you can with a shield and you can't stun with your parry.<br>
<br>
Since all the Weapons you can choose (Axe/Hammer/Sword) are purely strength based you shouldn't choose a high dex class.<br>
<br>
But DO IT, if you like to play like a fast sneaky little kobold, who likes to flank enemy groups an assault the healer! It's a RPG after all!<br>
<br>
I'm a european player, we got patch 1.60 onlione and I must say, that Skalds are still far from being a weak class.<br>
<br>
Group vs. Group - very high capabilities<br>
<br>
- You can mezz and snare to save your healer<br>
- You can deal about 350- 500 dmg in one shot easily (Hit+DD+DD) to finish an opponent before any enemy healer get's the chance to save him<br>
- You help your group a lot with your dmg song! In normal Grp vs. Grp you will fight right beside your teammates (assist...) or you are doing something wrong<br>
- you are one of the best interruptors in the game<br>
<br>
Army vs. Army - medium capabilities<br>
<br>
- You can still be a good &quot;finisher&quot; but you lack defense or range to be the first to charge or to protect the casters perfectly.<br>
<br>
Keep Defense / Raid - very low capabilities<br>
<br>
- Without a shield and the walls full of archers...<br>
- The range of your spells is simply too low to reach the walls effectively<br>
- Best thing to do is to make a ram<br>
<br>
1vs.1 - High capabilities<br>
<br>
- Despite the constant whining you are a pretty decent dueler. Kiting (dd+dd+mezz-&gt; recharge / run-&gt; dd+dd again...) still works. Try dd+dd+mezz-&gt;conquer (backstyle)-&gt;sledgehammer(chain follow up) with you Hammer and you will see, that you will have done 500-600 dmg in most cases, in the time, where you opponent has barely entered the fight at all.<br>
- you are one of the best interruptors in the game<br>
<br>
Spec + Gear<br>
<br>
I went all offensive. Try to finish a fight quick, don't give your opponent the chance to block, parry or evade a lot, because you won't yourself! 46/46/10 Hammer is my Spec. Don't give up the last dmg song! It really helps your group as mentioned above!<br>
<br>
I chose dd reactive procs + dmg shield charges on the armor parts. (Partly still in epic) and the obligatory DoT Proc on the Hammer. Dmg to your opponent is important to finish the fight quicker imho.<br>
<br>
Last but not least: make a few nice &quot;Norse Rhyme macros&quot; - your are a poet after all!<br>
<br>
